<TITLE> Khaleda's statement positive: adviser </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 20 (bdnews24.com)  An adviser on Thursday termed BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia's statement on being ready for elections on Dec 28 as "positive". Commerce and education adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman told reporters he hoped that the nation could achieve solutions through "the responsible participation of all parties." BNP and its allies will go to the general election on Dec. 28, if conditions are met, Khaleda announced in a televised briefing after back-to-back meetings of her party and the four-party alliance on Thursday. He was replying to questions from the newsmen at the DU VC's residence, after talks on how to resolve the complaints of the 27th BCS 'first batch' qualifiers, who failed to pass in the second-round results. bdnews24
